
Basics

Installation
# yum install screen

Usage
$ screen -L
ctl-A?
ctl-Ad
$ screen -ls
$ screen -r <pid>

Popular Commands
1) Enter Help: ctl-A? 
2) Exit Help: <spacebar>
3) Enter Screen: screen
4) Detach Screen: ctl-Ad
5) Kill Screen: ctl-AK
6) Re-attach Screen: screen -r
7) List active detached screens: screen -ls
8) Enable Screen Logging: ctl-AH, or screen -L

Also available but I've not yet used
1) lock screen
2) set password

